The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Serena to play in Bangalore

 WTA Meet 

Bangalore: Serena Williams is set to enthral Indian audience with her brand of power hitting when she appears for the first time in the country in the Sony Ericsson International to be held here at the KSLTA Stadium from February 12-18 next year. 

Sania Mirza would be the other star attraction in this 32-draw, $1,75,000 prize money tournament to be co-hosted by the Karnataka government and Karnatake State Lawn Tennis Association. 

Sania said she was looking forward to playing in the event. I look forward to the newly-created Tier-III tournament, she said here on Monday. 

Serena said, Im very excited to be playing in Bangalore. Tennis as a sport has become more and more popular in India and I hope many fans of all ages will come out and see us play. 

(PTI) 




